Spatial cell clustering of VisiumHD data by MEcell

Qi Liu

20 June, 2025

  • Load the library and the seurat object
  • Build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell), followed by clustering
  • Cell types of interest:hippocampus, Corpus Callosum, Leptomeningeal cells in the outer layer, Pvi

Load the library and the seurat object

library(MEcell)
library(ggplot2)

# The data have already been log-normalized, scaled and RunPCA using Seurat
#The Seurat object contains raw counts,normalized data, and PCA embeddings

obj<-readRDS(url("https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/kk1wyyki1ytpoa6gx5laq/visiumHD_brain.rds?rlkey=k4nksnkmt1klrnlkjfglnr0xn&dl=1"))

Build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell), followed by clustering

# build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell)
#set usepca=TRUE to use PCA scores to create microenvironment profile since VisiumHD is a whole-transcriptome platform

obj<-MEcell(obj,usepca = T)

#clustering on the MEcell SNN graph
obj<-FindClusters(obj,graph.name = "MEcell",verbose = F)

#Visualizing cell clustering
ImageDimPlot(obj,group.by="MEcell_res.0.8")+ ggtitle("MEcell clustering")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+scale_y_reverse()

Cell types of interest:hippocampus, Corpus Callosum, Leptomeningeal cells in the outer layer, Pvi

## 17:DG, 18:CA1, 20:CA3, 22: Corpus Callosum, 6: Leptomeningeal cells, 25:PVi
ImageDimPlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(6,25,17,18,20,21,25)])+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))+scale_y_reverse()

ImageFeaturePlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(6,25,17,18,20,21,25)],features =c("Ptgds","Apod","Ccn2","Nnat"))
